HEADWORD: Sheading
<hw>Shead"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From AS.
<ets>sc⟦amac⟧dan</ets>, <ets>sce⟦aacute⟧dan</ets>, to separate, divide.
See <er>Shed</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A tithing, or division,
in the Isle of Man, in which there is a coroner, or chief constable. The
island is divided into six sheadings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

